A 50-year-old police captain was shot and wounded while conducting a search operation in Manenberg. CAPE TOWN - Another police officer has been shot and wounded, this time in Manenberg.The captain was conducting a search operation for illegal firearms and drugs when he and his colleagues came under attack on Thursday morning.The police s Andre Traut says the gunman fled the scene. The circumstances surround an attack on police officers are being investigated following an incident in Manenberg, where a 50-year-old police captain was shot and wounded while performing duties in the area. Meanwhile, police are on the hunt for two suspects in connection with an attack on two officers in Philippi East on Tuesday night.Constable Amanda Ladlokova was shot and killed and a 39-year-old Sergeant is fighting for his life in hospital. Their firearms were stolen.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)